  "body": "I just updated my Geth docker, using the same config file as before and now I get this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO [08-13|15:57:50.958] Starting Geth on GÃ¶rli testnet...\r\nFatal: /data/config/geth.toml, line 141: field 'GraphQLHost' is not defined in node.Config, see https://godoc.org/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/node#Config for available fields\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf I go to the address listed and search \"GraphQL\" I only see `DefaultGraphQLHost`, I thought maybe this config flag just changed its name so I tried that and I get:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFatal: /data/config/geth.toml, line 143: field 'DefaultGraphQLPort' is not defined in node.Config, see https://godoc.org/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/node#Config for available fields\r\n```\r\n\r\nI tested with `latest` and `stable` same thing.\r\n\r\nSo, it looks like the latest release broke that flag?\r\n\r\nDefault config dump is:\r\n```\r\n[Node]\r\nDataDir = \"/root/.ethereum\"\r\nIPCPath = \"geth.ipc\"\r\nHTTPHost = \"\"\r\nHTTPPort = 8545\r\nHTTPVirtualHosts = [\"localhost\"]\r\nHTTPModules = [\"net\", \"web3\", \"eth\"]\r\nWSHost = \"\"\r\nWSPort = 8546\r\nWSModules = [\"net\", \"web3\", \"eth\"]\r\nGraphQLVirtualHosts = [\"localhost\"]\r\n```\r\n\r\nSame thing for the `GraphQLPort`",
